# Workshop Sample API — CLAUDE.md

## Project Overview

This is a Node.js REST API for managing vehicle data.
Express.js backend with in-memory storage.

## Build & Run

- Install: `npm install`
- Start: `npm start` (runs on port 3000)
- Test: `npm test` (uses Node.js built-in test runner)

## Code Style

- Use ES6+ features (const/let, arrow functions, template literals)
- Use `===` for strict equality, never `==`
- Add JSDoc comments for all exported functions
- Error responses must include an `error` field with a descriptive message

## Architecture

- `src/index.js` — Express app setup and routes
- `src/api.js` — Route handlers (controller layer)
- `src/utils.js` — Pure utility functions (testable)
- `src/config.js` — Configuration (should use env vars)
- `test/` — Unit tests using Node.js test runner

## Conventions

- HTTP status codes: 200 (OK), 201 (Created), 400 (Bad Request), 404 (Not Found)
- All API routes under `/api/` prefix
- Input validation before any data mutation
- Never commit secrets or credentials to code

